The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically learning distributed representations of texts and knowledge base entities. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses a neural network model, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) tasks such as entity linking and factoid question answering, which could place it in cs.IR. Finally, the paper uses a large corpus of texts and entity annotations extracted from Wikipedia, which suggests it could also belong to cs.DB (Databases).
